explanation: The solution uses a stack to keep track of characters that cannot be removed. It iterates through the string, and for each character, it checks if the top of the stack has the same character. If it does, it removes the top of the stack; otherwise, it adds the character to the stack. The length of the final stack is the minimum length of the string.

